                <head>141. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>In a memorandum to the Secretary, November 27, Assistant Secretary of State
                        <persName corresp="#p_ECB1">Elbrick</persName> had indicated that the
                    Italian Embassy had informed the Department of State that Foreign Minister
                        <persName corresp="#p_PG1">Giuseppe Pella</persName> wished to meet with
                        <persName>Dulles</persName> as a form of preliminary consultation prior to
                    the <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> Heads of Government Meeting in Paris
                    (December 16–19). <persName>Dulles</persName> approved <persName
                        corresp="#p_ECB1">Elbrick</persName>’s recommendation that he meet with
                        <persName corresp="#p_PG1">Pella</persName>. (Department of State, Central
                    Files, 765.13/11–2757)</p>
                <p>The memoranda of conversation covering the meetings in Washington among
                        <persName>Dulles</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_PG1">Pella</persName>,
                    and their advisers on December 6 indicate that questions pertaining to <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>, the Middle East, and disarmament were
                    discussed. (<hi rend="italic">Ibid.,</hi> Secretary’s Memoranda of Conversation:
                    Lot 64 D199)</p>
            </div>
